Amazon Linux Ec2 instance:

sudo yum update -y
sudo yum install -y python3
sudo python3 -m ensurepip
sudo python3 -m pip install --upgrade pip
pip3 --version
pip3 install Flask

cat t.py
from flask import Flask

app = Flask(__name__)

@app.route('/')
def hello():
    return "<h1>Hello from Flask Web Server!</h1>"

if __name__ == '__main__':
    app.run(host='0.0.0.0', port=5000)


Run web server in background:
nohup python3 t.py > t.log 2>&1 &

On your laptop open web browser and type http://<public-ip-ec2>:5000 , hello world web page opens up !!!!!!

